 **React-based PWA**, optimized for Android TV, directly integrating with **Google Photos API** and **OpenWeatherMap** (no backend middleware).
production-grade Product Requirements Document (PRD)** for **Digital FotoFrame**, 

---

## üìò PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)

### Product Name: **Digital FotoFrame (PWA for Android TV)**

### Version: 1.0

### Owner: Product Owner (You)

### Platform: Android TV (Progressive Web App)

---

### 1. üéØ Product Vision

**Digital FotoFrame** transforms any Android TV into a smart, connected photo frame that auto-displays personal photos from **USB/local storage** or **Google Photos albums**.
It aims to provide a **hands-free, minimalist, ambient experience** that feels native to the TV ‚Äî with auto-sync, weather overlays, and elegant motion effects.

---

### 2. üß≠ Objectives

* Create a **full-screen, distraction-free slideshow** experience.
* Enable **quick setup** via QR-based Google account linking.
* Support **multiple users and persistent login sessions**.
* Offer **deep personalization** ‚Äî clock, transitions, brightness, music, etc.
* Integrate **live weather and time overlays** seamlessly.
* Work **offline** when showing USB/local photos.

---

### 3. üë• Target Users

* Home users wanting a personal digital photo frame experience.
* Families sharing albums via Google Photos.
* Retail or hospitality setups needing rotating image displays.

---

### 4. üß© Core Features & Requirements

#### 4.1 Landing / Welcome Screen

* Full-screen welcome logo animation (‚ÄúDigital FotoFrame‚Äù).
* Options displayed in large tiles:

  1. **Select Folder (USB/Local)**
  2. **Connect Google Photos Account (QR Login)**
* Persistent top bar:

  * **Left:** ‚öôÔ∏è *Customize* button
  * **Right:** üåô *Theme Toggle* (Light / Dark)

---

#### 4.2 Folder Source: USB / Local Storage

* Detect connected USB storage and list folder hierarchy.
* Allow user to select one or more folders.
* Option to enable recursive scanning (include subfolders).
* Auto-start slideshow once folder(s) are selected.

---

#### 4.3 Google Photos Integration

* Show ‚ÄúConnect Google Account‚Äù tile with QR code.
* QR leads to OAuth consent screen on user‚Äôs mobile.
* After successful login, app stores access token locally (indexedDB/localStorage).
* User selects **specific albums** to include in the slideshow.
* Automatically syncs new photos if added to the same albums.
* Supports multiple Google accounts ‚Äî user can switch accounts.
* Persist login session across reboots until manual logout.

---

#### 4.4 Slideshow Mode

* Auto slideshow starts when source (local or Google Photos) is ready.
* Transition effects supported:

  * **Fade, Pan, Zoom, Slide, Ken Burns effect**.
* Slideshow interval customizable (default: 8s).
* Smooth cross-fades between photos.
* Local caching of next N images for seamless transitions.
* Background color adapts to theme.
* Optional background ambient music (toggleable).

---

#### 4.5 Customization Panel (Top Left)

Accessible anytime (overlay or via remote ‚ÄúMenu‚Äù key).

| Setting Category   | Options                                                     |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Clock**          | Show/Hide, Position (4 corners), Analog/Digital, 12/24-hour |
| **Font & Display** | Font family (2‚Äì3), Font size slider                         |
| **Transitions**    | Ken Burns, Pan, Zoom, Fade, Slide                           |
| **Interval**       | Adjustable (3‚Äì30 sec)                                       |
| **Visuals**        | Brightness / Contrast / Transparency                        |
| **Startup**        | Auto-start slideshow on TV boot                             |
| **Audio**          | Enable/Disable ambient music, select from preset tracks     |
| **Weather Widget** | On/Off toggle                                               |
| **Logout**         | Logout current Google account                               |

---

#### 4.6 Weather Widget

* Uses **OpenWeatherMap API**.
* Fetches weather based on **geolocation or user-set city**.
* Displays temperature + weather icon (top-right overlay).
* Refreshes every 15 minutes.

---

#### 4.7 Theming

* Global toggle (top-right icon).
* Two themes:

  * **Light:** clean white with subtle gray overlays.
  * **Dark:** black background, neon/gray minimal overlays.
* Theme applies to all screens, saved in local storage.

---

### 5. üß≠ User Flows

#### 5.1 First Launch

```
[Welcome Screen] ‚Üí Choose Source ‚Üí (USB Folder / Google Photos) ‚Üí Slideshow Starts
```

#### 5.2 Google Login Flow

```
Show QR ‚Üí Scan via Mobile ‚Üí Google OAuth Consent ‚Üí Redirects to success ‚Üí TV auto-links ‚Üí Album Selection ‚Üí Slideshow
```

#### 5.3 Customization Flow

```
Slideshow ‚Üí Press Menu / Customize ‚Üí Overlay Panel ‚Üí Adjust Settings ‚Üí Auto-save Preferences
```

---

### 6. üñ•Ô∏è UI / UX Design Principles

* **Minimalist:** full-bleed images, subtle overlays only when necessary.
* **TV-Optimized Layout:** navigation via D-Pad + OK button.
* **Large Targets:** 48px min button height.
* **Animations:** use `react-spring` or `framer-motion` for smooth transitions.
* **Responsive:** scales to 1080p and 4K TVs.
* **Fonts:** Sans-serif, high contrast for readability.

---

### 7. üß± Technical Architecture

| Component                | Technology                                                           |
| ------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Frontend Framework**   | React + TypeScript                                                   |
| **UI Framework**         | Tailwind CSS / Material UI                                           |
| **Routing**              | React Router                                                         |
| **Storage**              | IndexedDB for tokens, settings, and local cache                      |
| **Authentication**       | Google OAuth 2.0 (via QR + device linking flow)                      |
| **APIs**                 | Google Photos REST API, OpenWeatherMap API                           |
| **PWA Capabilities**     | Service Worker caching, offline fallback for local folders           |
| **TV Remote Navigation** | DPAD events + focus management via `react-tv-navigation`             |
| **Build Target**         | Android TV WebView or browser-based app launcher                     |
| **Deployment**           | Hosted as HTTPS PWA, installable via TV browser ‚ÄúAdd to Home Screen‚Äù |

---

### 8. ‚öôÔ∏è Non-Functional Requirements

| Category          | Requirement                                                             |
| ----------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Performance**   | Load within 3s; maintain 60 FPS transitions                             |
| **Offline Mode**  | USB/local slideshow must work fully offline                             |
| **Security**      | Store OAuth tokens securely in local storage (refresh tokens encrypted) |
| **Reliability**   | Resume last slideshow on restart                                        |
| **Scalability**   | Support up to 10,000 photos in rotation                                 |
| **Compatibility** | Android TV OS 10+ (Chromium-based WebView)                              |
| **Localization**  | English (v1); extensible for future i18n                                |
| **Accessibility** | Font scaling; minimal color flashing                                    |
| **Logging**       | Local-only (no cloud analytics)                                         |

---

### 9. üîÑ Future Enhancements

* **AI-powered face clustering** (‚ÄúShow only family/friends‚Äù)
* **Voice control via Google Assistant**
* **OneDrive / Dropbox integration**
* **Smart album rotation based on seasons or events**
* **Companion mobile app for remote customization**

---

### 10. üìã Acceptance Criteria Summary

| Feature       | Acceptance Criteria                                      |
| ------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| Google Login  | QR-based auth works and session persists post-reboot     |
| Slideshow     | Automatically starts after folder selection              |
| USB Access    | Can browse and select folder(s) successfully             |
| Customization | All settings instantly reflected in slideshow            |
| Theme Toggle  | Immediate UI switch between light/dark                   |
| Weather       | Displays correct live data from OpenWeatherMap           |
| Multi-User    | Can switch between Google accounts without reinstall     |
| Offline Mode  | Works fully offline for local photos                     |
| Auto Sync     | Detects new Google Photos in linked album within 15 mins |

---

### 11. üß≠ User Stories (Sample)

1. As a user, I want to **scan a QR code on TV** to log into Google Photos without typing credentials.
2. As a user, I want to **select specific albums** from my Google Photos for the slideshow.
3. As a user, I want to **customize slideshow effects and speed** to match my preferences.
4. As a user, I want the **clock and weather widget** to appear unobtrusively during slideshow.
5. As a user, I want the **TV to auto-start slideshow on boot** so I don‚Äôt have to reopen the app.

